                    <comment id="12837358" author="anchela" created="Tue, 23 Feb 2010 18:22:23 +0000"  >executing the code provided by stefan works if executed in spi2jcr but not with spi2dav(ex).&lt;br/&gt;
i therefore assume that this is a problem with workspace-move in spi2dav -&amp;gt; changing component accordingly.</comment>
                    <comment id="12837422" author="anchela" created="Tue, 23 Feb 2010 20:06:01 +0000"  >the problem occurs both with workspace and with session move and is caused by the uri-lookup that isn&amp;#39;t adjusted.&lt;br/&gt;
since that part of the spi2dav is marked with TODOs and needs to be reviewed anyway, i will add a simple fix that just&lt;br/&gt;
clears the lookup after successful move without making expensive checks if a node having a uniqueID part in the NodeID&lt;br/&gt;
was part of the moved tree.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
in addition i will add a testcase to jcr2spi (thanks for the code-sniplet)</comment>
